n (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage AI agent runtime configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing the foundation for sandbox orchestration and lifecycle management.\\n6: \\n7: The `AgentRuntime` resource represents a configurable agent execution environment with support for:\\n8: - Code interpreter attachment\\n9: - Resource quotas (CPU, memory, storage)\\n10: - Network policies and egress rules\\n11: - Lifecycle hooks (preStart, postStop)\\n12: - Status tracking (phase, conditions, sandbox reference)\\n13: \\n14: ## Scope\\n15: \\n16: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \\n17: **API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \\n18: **Kind:** `AgentRuntime` (namespaced)  \\n19: **Size:** S\\n20: \\n21: ### In Scope\\n22: \\n23: 1. **Type Definitions** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`)\\n24:    - `AgentRuntime` - main resource struct\\n25:    - `AgentRuntimeSpec` - desired state specification\\n26:    - `AgentRuntimeStatus` - observed state status\\n27:    - `CodeInterpreterSpec` - embedded code interpreter configuration\\n28:    - `ResourceQuota` - sandbox resource limits\\n29:    - `NetworkPolicy` - egress/ingress rules\\n30:    - `LifecycleHook` ...\n  Line 31: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775839655308,\"sessionID\":\"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d784a8a04001aBmGXxEp505as8\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d784a8108001qlPk6b2kFBEmZ8\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Based on my analysis of the AR-001 change archive:\\n\\n## AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\\n\\n**Module:** pkg/apis  \\n**Language:** Go  \\n**Size:** S\\n\\n---\\n\\n### ✅ Completed\\n\\n1. **Scaffold directory structure**\\n   - `pkg/apis/runtime/register.go` - API group registration\\n   - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` - complete directory structure\\n\\n2. **Type Definitions** (`types.go`)\\n   - `AgentRuntimePhase` enum (Pending, Running, Failed, Terminatin